title: Walt Whitman to Richard Maurice Bucke, 10 October 1890
text: CamdenPM Oct: 10 '90Nothing very different with me—fair enough—Did I tell you I sent off "Old Poets" (5 pages—maybe minus) to N[orth] A[merican] Rev[iew]?—(I rec'd yesterday mn'g a telegram f'm them soliciting it)—I guess the Ing[ersoll] enterprise continues to move well—Horace is nearer excited than I ever saw him—I was out an hour in wheel-chair yesterday—am very susceptible to the jolting—always come back with a confused, topsy-turvy head-achy feeling—sunny to-day—Enclose two MSS the O'C[onnor] preface & the little Shakspere bit, (both w'd take prize for dilapitated printer's copy)—we are surfeited with horrible murder cases & such, here—then visits f'm the g't miners engineers & the French prince—I welcome all—Walt Whitman Walt Whitman to Richard Maurice Bucke, 10 October 1890
